e and the brewing process continues. This process deepens the malt character and adds a subtle toffee backbone to this delicious lager.\n\nWeâ€™ve added Magnum hops for bittering and Czech Saaz hops for aroma to create a classic European Noble hop flavor. \n\nScratch #6-2007 is unfiltered, so there will be a slight haze to the beer.','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Scratch #6 2007',0,95,0,1286),(4650,0,0,1,'','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','McNellie\'s Pub Ale',0,4,0,831),(4651,0,0,11,'','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Sundown Wheat',0,116,0,831),(4652,0,0,3,'','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Atlas IPA',0,31,0,831),(4653,7.199999809265137,0,3,'Arrogant Bastard Ale aged in oak barrels.','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Oaked Arrogant Bastard Ale',0,30,0,1204),(4654,4.800000190734863,0,8,'Surviving beer from the Dortmunder Hansa-Brauerei before being acquired by Actien.','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Hansa Imported Dortmunder',0,95,0,460),(4655,0,0,4,'It is a nice example of a Hefeweizen.','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Hoppy Hefe',0,50,0,90),(4656,0,0,2,'Think of Guinness but with a \"smooth bite\"\" to it. This is a wonder beer for those of us who enjoy a porter.\"','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Bourbon Barrel Smoked Porter',0,25,0,90),(4657,0,0,-1,'It does have a nice hint of wheat and blueberries to it.','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Bar Harbor Blueberry Ale',0,-1,0,55),(4658,0,0,4,'It is a good clean hefe.','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Cask Hefe',0,50,0,90),(4659,8,0,3,'A deep, mahogany ale brewed with beet sugar, green raisins, and Belgian-style yeast. As complex as a fine, red wine. Voted \"American Beer of the Year\"\" in January 2000 by Malt Advocate Magazine.\"','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Raison D\'Etre',0,29,0,459),(4660,18,0,11,'A strong ale brewed with a ridiculous amount of pureed raspberries (over a ton of em!).','',0,'2010-07-22 20:00:20 UTC','Fort',0,121,0,459),(4661,4,0,3,'Lawnmower is our intro for those who need a little help jumping 