d palate which gives the beer a well rounded balance.','',0,'2011-05-17 03:27:08 UTC','2008 Culture Beer',0,3,0,1412),(5892,7.199999809265137,462,1,'English Style India Pale Ale, Maris Otter 2-row, Canadian Honey Malt and Belgian Crystal.\nCentennial, Kent Golding, and Cascade are added Five times during the process, including Dry Hopping.\n\nAroma: Earthy, Citrusy, and Resinous\nTasting/Flavor: Orangy and Sugary Apricots\nFinish: Malt Sweetness Balanced by Dry Hops','',0,'2011-05-23 10:39:09 UTC','Iron Rail IPA',0,2,0,1413),(5893,0,483,11,'Porter is a dark-coloured beer developed in the 1750s. Porter has a heavier flavour and aroma and a slightly sweet taste. Its name probably originates in the belief that this strong, nourishing drink was ideal for hard-working porters and labourers. Black Creek Porter is wonderful on its own, or with salty snacks.\n\n','',0,'2011-06-08 07:10:06 UTC','Black Creek Porter',0,130,0,1414),(5894,9.25,494,5,'A classic golden ale, with subtle esters of banana and bubblegum. This beer pours with a creamy head and ends with a sweetness of light Belgian candi sugars. Our brewmaster aged this ale for an extended period to round out the flavors. A great traditional Belgian brew. ','',0,'2011-06-22 12:22:12 UTC','Vivant Tripel',0,61,0,1416),(5895,7.099999904632568,516,3,'','',0,'2011-07-07 07:43:36 UTC','Watershed IPA',0,30,0,1417),(5896,7.099999904632568,516,3,'','',0,'2011-07-07 07:44:10 UTC','Watershed IPA',0,30,0,1417),(5897,4.800000190734863,524,9,'','',0,'2011-07-14 08:52:30 UTC','Estrella Levante Clasica',0,106,0,1087),(5898,5.400000095367432,524,9,'','',0,'2011-07-14 08:53:33 UTC','Estrella Levante Especial',0,106,0,1087),(5899,1,524,9,'','',0,'2011-07-14 08:54:53 UTC','Estrella Levante Sin 0.0% Alcohol',0,106,0,1087),(5900,5,535,11,'Japanese Rice Lager','echigo_bottle.jpg',0,'2011-07-23 20:37:34 UTC','Koshihikari Echigo Beer',0,132,0,1419),(5901,0,539,11,'','',0,'2011-07-28 19:06:02 UTC','Full Boar',0,132,0,1420),(5902,6,553,3,'The Pu